    "The main disadvantage of the approach is that it is unclear how well the states approximate the long-time evolution and that a matrix inversion on noisy measurement results is necessary, which is often unstable.",
    "Recently a first implementation of the variational time evolution based on optimization was implemented on IBM quantum computers simulating the Heisenberg model with 3 qubits 129.",
    "The results suggest an improvement over the pure Trotterized approach but simulations for larger systems also demonstrate that the required circuit depth scales linearly with the entanglement induced due to the time evolution.",
